news.title: China Evergrande says winding-up lawsuit won't impact restructuring
news.para: Evergrande confirmed the filing by investment holding firm Top Shine Global Ltd in Hong Kong for not fulfilling a financial obligation of HK$862.5 million ($109.91 million).

news.title: Awfis lease out 65,000 sq ft space to UNext in Bengaluru
news.para: In February 2022, the company had leased 85,000 sq ft space with 1,500 seats in River Side Tower, sector 125, Noida.

news.title: Nagpur survey office mutates land with 800 plots, houses in name of five
news.para: NIT counsel Girish Kunte, following the directives of trust chairman, had fought a four-year-long battle and got the properties registered in NIT’s name again.

news.title: IT Park housing scheme in Chandigarh secures wildlife clearance
news.para: The decision was taken in a meeting of the state wildlife board held under the chairmanship of UT administrator Banwarilal Purohit on Monday.

news.title: Carlyle acquires significant minority stake in Ahmedabad-based Varmora Granito
news.para: Equity for this transaction will come from funds managed and advised by entities affiliated with Carlyle Asia Partners Growth, the US private equity firm said in a statement.

news.title: Jharkhand: Stone dust replaces sand for construction
news.para: Bokaro Steel plant (BSL) and the Research and Development Centres for Iron and Steel (RDCIS) are working to explore possibilities of developing slag sand generated during steel production as another substitute for sand.

news.title: ED takes custody of ABIL group chairman in money laundering case
news.para: ​The Pune-based businessman had earlier been arrested by the Central Bureau of Investigation (CBI) in connection with an alleged corruption case involving Yes Bank founder Rana Kapoor and Kapil Wadhawan of the DHFL.

news.title: Illegal dumping of building waste at 314 spots: Gurugram civic body's survey
news.para: The major challenge now before MCG is to lift this waste before monsoon arrives as waste continues to clog several drains and aggravate waterlogging on roads when it rains.

news.title: Indiabulls Real Estate guilty of profiteering Rs 6.46 crore, to refund buyers: NAA
news.para: ​Based on a case filed by a homebuyer that Indiabulls Real Estate has not passed on ITC benefits in project Sierra-Vizag, situated in Visakhapatnam, the Directorate General of Anti Profiteering (DGAP) investigated the case and found the builder guilty of profiteering.

news.title: HC pauses auction of 40 vacant plots by Hyderabad development body
news.para: Justice P Madhavi Devi pronounced the order after hearing the 2018 petition filed by the association opposing the proposed auction of plots by HMDA.

news.title: Chetan Bhagat buys south Delhi apartment for Rs 11.6 crore
news.para: Chetan Bhagat paid Rs 70 lakh stamp duty for the transaction. As per the listing on India Sotheby's International Realty, the apartment forms part of a building with a plot size of 410 sqm. The home in South Delhi with a built-up area of 270 sqm has 4 spacious bedrooms.

news.title: Telangana government receives 40,000 applications for 3,700 Swagruha flats
news.para: A notification for sale of 3,700 flats in Bandlaguda and Pocharam has already been issued and the response has been overwhelming.

news.title: Byju's leases 5.5 lakh sq ft office space in Bengaluru
news.para: The agreement has an escalation clause of 5% yearly on the previous year's rent, said Propstack, a real estate data company.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board calls for e-bids for 25 freehold properties
news.para: Out of the 23 residential properties, 17 are located in Indira Colony, Manimajra. Reserve price of the units ranges from Rs 32 lakh to Rs 34 lakh.

news.title: Residents in Ludhiana flag rising commercial activities in residential areas
news.para: ​The situation is such that commercial activity is being allowed in every nook and corner without a thought to the parking and traffic issues.
